1. *Uobičajeno* vreme za večeru je oko osam sati. (*Uobičajeno* - Adverb, at the beginning of the sentence) (The usual time for dinner is around 8 o'clock.)
2. Vreme za večeru je *uobičajeno* oko osam sati. (*Uobičajeno* - Adverb, in the middle of the sentence) (Dinner time is usually around 8 o'clock.)
3. *Uobičajeno* je da se ljudi druže vikendom. (*Uobičajeno* - Adverb, at the beginning of the sentence) (It's usual for people to socialize on weekends.)
4. Ljudi se *uobičajeno* druže vikendom. (*Uobičajeno* - Adverb, in the middle of the sentence) (People usually socialize on weekends.)
5. Njihov *uobičajeni* način života je vrlo zdrav. (*Uobičajeni* - Adjective) (Their usual way of life is very healthy.)
6. *Uobičajena* praksa je da se ljudi pozdravljaju kad se sretnu. (*Uobičajena* - Adjective) (The usual practice is for people to greet each other when they meet.)
7. Govoriti o politici je *uobičajeno* na večerama. (*Uobičajeno* - Adverb, at the beginning of the sentence) (Talking about politics is usual at dinners.)
8. Na večerama je *uobičajeno* govoriti o politici. (*Uobičajeno* - Adverb, in the middle of the sentence) (It's usual to talk about politics at dinners.)